Ahhhhh I am sooo excited to finally share this with you!!

Although we had initially planned this to look a little different pre-COVID, we were determined to make it happen one way or another!!

I want to give back to YOU and truly show you what YOU have taught me about loving myself, being comfortable in my own skin and BEING confident!

HOW TO WIN🔥
❤️post a photo or video of you feeling your most confident!
❤️hashtag #actconfidentchallenge and tag @sarahs_day and @whitefoxboutique 
❤️WORLDWIDE entires accepted! Challenge closes on the 14th of Feb

🥰be confident, have fun with it and EMBRACE YOU!!!

node.text:
NO EQUIPMENT workout to get your heart rate up, encourage circulation and get the MOST out of a short workout!!

45 seconds on 15 seconds off
Complete 4 rounds of each exercise as a quick outdoor HIIT burner!!🔥☀️

Each week of lockdown I’ve found myself gravitating towards a different workout style. First it was weights in our garage, then it was low impact Pilates, now it’s outdoor full body workouts with minimal-no equipment. 

What are your fave style of workouts/exercises to see on my page??💕🧚🏼‍♀️

node.text:
STAIRCASE WORKOUT🍑🔥
6 Rounds of each exercise
30 secs ON // 10 secs REST

(30 secs rest before you start the next exercise)

This was my first workout back after having a tough 2 weeks. I tried to do a workout a few days ago but I felt my increasing heart rate negatively affecting my emotions and as I began to sweat I also began to cry. However, today was different, although my heart is still heavy, working out boosted my mood and overall mental health. This is why it’s so important to listen to our bodies and take each day as it comes. 

I HIGHLY recommend giving this workout a go. I think it was a mixture of being outside and utilising exercises that really get the blood pumping that made it so enjoyable!

P.s this is me filling my soul with worship music that also motivates me to workout😂👏🏼🙏🏼

node.text:
Lockdown style office🌴☀️
Yep, here in Sydney we are heading into week 11 of lockdown (I think…I’ve kind of lost count at this point)
Just like smashing out a uni assignment on my laptop back in the day, I’ve been moving around the house working. The past few weeks this spot here has been my productive pad!
I’m curious to know…

1. Are you currently in lockdown?
2. If you’re working from home, what’s your fave place/room to work from!?

node.text:
Feeling very, very special and loved right now💕🌸
I’d be lying if I said I was excited for my birthday this year. My mind cloudy and drained from some emotional family stuff going on and coming into week 11 of lockdown, I just didn’t want to acknowledge the day. 

Yesterday I cried happy tears. Thank you to all my friends, family and even you sneaky gals out there (you know who you are) who sent me flowers, gifts and even just DM’s wishing me a happy birthday!

It was a simple day full of chocolate, takeaway toasties, ramen, pink balloons and hanging out with my two boys. 

This is a pic of my kitchen today. I never want these flowers to fall because walking through this space is an absolute fairytale right now!!🧚🏼‍♀️✨

node.text:
Embracing 2010 and debuting Fox’s first official peace and pout selfie😂
Feeling more grateful than ever for this mini-me🦊Foxy has been my real life teddy bear giving my endless cuddles, patting my head and making me laugh even when my heart feels heavy. 
Thank you all for being SO incredibly kind, gentle and supportive this week. Even if I haven’t had the strength or words to respond, I have been reading all of your DM’s and feeling encouraged that I’m uplifted by such a strong and loving community🤍🤍 #Godisgood

node.text:
Homemade trail mix I make for Fox Ocean🥰

I make small batches at a time as I love to mix it up and surprise Fox (and Kurt) with different trail mix combinations.

This week was an absolute HIT!! 
Shredded Coconut
Dried Apricot
Dried Figs
Dried Apple
Pumpkin Seeds
Sunflower Seeds
Slivered Almonds
Choc Chips (our a dairy free but use any you like!)

A little look at a week of toddler play in lockdown… (pssst make it 60* seconds)

THIS is what I’m meant to be doing!!! Toddler mum is my FAVE stage of LIFE so far!! Foxy is almost 2.5 and he is legitimately sooo much fun to hang out with!!

We’ve been doing a lot of outside play in the backyard and feeding his creative passions. Here’s a list of some of our fave activities this week…

🎨watercolour painting/regular painting on the easel
✍️drawing people and trucks with our new texters and crayons
🌴pretend fishing in the pool and kicking our feet in the water
🕺🏼DANCING all day every day
👯‍♀️learning dances, playing freeze and repeating actions
🤸🏼‍♂️practising forward rolls and hanging off the rings/bar
🍪 helping mum cook healthy treats

node.text:
Appreciating these textured white walls as I scrolled through some old house renovation images today😂

This is our upstairs guest bathroom that we have unexpectedly been using A LOT! Since fox has been sleeping in our room, I’ll usually unwind and do my nighttime routine in here. 

When designing our bathrooms I wanted them to be timeless, textured, warm and fresh! We used natural terrazo, handmade matte tile in mis-matched rectangle and square shapes, along with brushed gold hardware. For a bathroom I didn’t think too hard about…it’s one of my fave places to unwind and freshen up!

FINISHED HOME TOUR COMING SOON!!
I was waiting for a few minor projects to get finished but with no end of lockdown in site, I may just film it now!!
